{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17640043","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17640043"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:11:15+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:11:15+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17797"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17797","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17797"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0,0,0.93,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10511"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79294"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10511","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10511"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17797"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64616"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"9926"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24535"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25022"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79294","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79294"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe medullary respiratory centre is a crucial component of respiratory control.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary function of the medullary respiratory centre?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Controls voluntary breathing movements exclusively","Regulates bronchial smooth muscle tone only","Processes pain signals from the respiratory tract","Generates respiratory rhythm and controls basic breathing pattern","Coordinates swallowing reflexes during respiration"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emedullary respiratory centre generates the basic rhythm of breathing and controls the respiratory pattern\u003C/strong\u003E. It contains groups of neurons that coordinate inspiration and expiration, with the pre-B\u00f6tzinger complex acting as the primary rhythm generator.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EControls voluntary breathing movements exclusively\u003C/strong\u003E - The medullary centre primarily controls automatic breathing; voluntary control comes from the cortex\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERegulates bronchial smooth muscle tone only\u003C/strong\u003E - Bronchial tone is primarily controlled by the autonomic nervous system, not the medullary respiratory centre\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProcesses pain signals from the respiratory tract\u003C/strong\u003E - Pain processing occurs primarily in other regions including the thalamus and cortex\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECoordinates swallowing reflexes during respiration\u003C/strong\u003E - While the medulla is involved in swallowing, this is not the primary function of the respiratory centre\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe medullary respiratory centre receives inputs from chemoreceptors, mechanoreceptors, and higher centres to adjust breathing rate and depth according to physiological needs.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The medullary respiratory centre contains the dorsal respiratory group which controls inspiration and the ventral respiratory group which controls expiration.","The pre-B\u00f6tzinger complex in the medulla generates the basic rhythm of breathing.","The medullary respiratory centre receives input from chemoreceptors and higher centres to modulate breathing rate and depth."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019","Hall J. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Elsevier Health Sciences; 2021. https://clinicalkeymeded.elsevier.com/reader/books/9780323597128"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64616"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17797"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64616","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64616"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-13T23:01:10+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-13T23:01:35+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10511"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79294"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"